Trader, wife in court for allegedly possessing counterfeit flour             Joseph Muchiri  28th Jan 2020 13:30:00 GMT +0300 Joseph Muchiri  28th Jan 2020 13:30:00 GMT +0300 Joseph Muchiri   John Muriithi and his wife, Mary Wachuka whenn they were presented in Gichugu law court in Kirinyaga County after allegedly being found in possession of counterfeit maize flour at their wholesale shop in Kianjokoma market in Embu County. [Joseph Muchiri, Standard]  John Muriithi and his wife, Mary Wachuka whenn they were presented in Gichugu law court in Kirinyaga County after allegedly being found in possession of counterfeit maize flour at their wholesale shop in Kianjokoma market in Embu County. [Joseph Muchiri, Standard] John Muriithi and his wife, Mary Wachuka whenn they were presented in Gichugu law court in Kirinyaga County after allegedly being found in possession of counterfeit maize flour at their wholesale shop in Kianjokoma market in Embu County. [Joseph Muchiri, Standard] John Muriithi and his wife, Mary Wachuka whenn they were presented in Gichugu law court in Kirinyaga County after allegedly being found in possession of counterfeit maize flour at their wholesale shop in Kianjokoma market in Embu County. [Joseph Muchiri, Standard]         For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » Subscribe Now »      jmuchiri@standardmedia.co.ke jmuchiri@standardmedia.co.ke  Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. HERE.  #mc_embed_signup{background:#fff; clear:left; font:14px Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; }
